RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5F All Weather Track CR: 76. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUSMA broke in a bit at the start and crowded EL CANELO, was forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the decent pace from a two wide path into the turn, inched closer to CORAL CAT in upper stretch, drew to even terms with that rival inside of the furlong marker, dueled to deep stretch, took a narrow lead inside of the sixteenth-marker and determinedly held on in the final stages to prevail. CORAL CAT broke sharply and showed speed to dictate terms in the early stages, set decent fractions to the quarter marker, came under pressure from LUSMA in upper stretch, met that bid at the furlong marker, dueled to deep stretch, lost the lead inside of the sixteenth-marker and was gamely bested in the final strides, while well clear of the rest. HALO RANDO chased the decent early pace into the turn, was a bit green and hard to place along the bend, swung three wide for the drive, raced on the left lead in the stretch, could not impact the top two in the final stages and ran on to secure third. TWELVE VOLT broke out at the start, lacked early speed, swung two wide into the stretch, ran evenly in the drive and was outfinished for third. EL CANELO crowded at the start and was off slowly, recovered to chase from the second flight into the turn, saved ground to the quarter marker, chased the leaders into the stretch and tired in the final furlong. DADS DREAM raced close to the decent early pace while outside of rivals, lost ground while three wide on the turn, came four wide into the lane and tired.

ENTRY.OWNER: Jauregui Racing Stables Inc and Eplin Danny A

ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne

ENTRY.COMMENT: close up early,3wide turn,4wide into stretch,tired

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out,no early speed,2wide into stretch,evenly drive

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 81. Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Elig ibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPUN BEAUTIFUL sent to establish the early lead, showed the way to the turn, set solid fractions while well handled through the bend, drew to a clear at mid-stretch while kept to moderate urging, kept to task to deep stretch and drew away in the final stages. TORREY'S GIRL bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, chased from the rear into the turn, saved ground to the quarter marker, was coaxed along two wide into the drive, could not make headway on the winner in the stretch and ran on to be second best. BLUEBERRY MUFFIN broke alertly, ceded the early lead to SPUN BEAUTIFUL and stalked that rival through solid early fractions, came three wide into the stretch, lost position at the furlong marker, ran evenly in the final stages and was outfinished, while clear of the rest for third. TIZ A TIGER chased the solid early pace while outside of rivals, raced four wide to the quarter marker, could not keep pace in the drive and gave way. SMILING SALSA chased the solid early pace, raced three wide into the turn, shifted in leaving the quarter marker, was coaxed two wide into the stretch and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Torrey's Girl
ENTRY.OWNER: Gans Doug Jacobs Gary Katz Larry M Riggs Kevin Rudy Roman Shoemaker Trevor Smoli
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled start,chased inside,2wide into stretch,2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 76. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STEIN'S GIRL took back off of the solid early pace, tracked the leading pair through the backstretch run, saved ground into the far turn, was asked for run two wide at the top of the lane, improved position nearing the furlong pole, responded to steady urging in the drive, closed fast inside of the sixteenth-marker, caught SPANISH CHANNEL in deep stretch and kept to task in the end to prevail. SPANISH CHANNEL drifted in at the break and bothered DANGEROUS ILLUSION, showed early speed and dictated terms into the first turn, ceded the lead to FANTASTIC SECRET into the backstretch run and stalked that rival through decent fractions to the half-mile marker, chased the pacesetter to the quarter pole, loomed in upper stretch and assumed command nearing the furlong marker, was all out approaching the sixteenth-pole, could not hold off STEIN'S GIRL in deep stretch and just held for second at the finish. DANGEROUS ILLUSION was bothered by SPANISH CHANNEL at the start, took up and was away slowly, was unhurried while saving ground through the backstretch run, saved all of the ground to the quarter pole, was full of run approaching mid-stretch, finished well inside of the furlong marker, split foes at the sixteenth-pole, finished well in deep stretch and just missed for second at the wire. FANTASTIC SECRET forwardly placed in the early running, contested the pace with SPANISH CHANNEL then assumed command into the backstretch run, set solid fractions while on a clear lead into the far turn, extended the lead heading to the quarter marker, came under pressure in upper stretch, battled with SPANISH CHANNEL to the furlong pole, could not keep pace in deep stretch and weakened. CALIFORNIA GIGI settled off of the early pace, was caught four wide into the first turn then raced in the three path into the backstretch run, tracked the solid fractions to the half-mile marker, lost ground while two then three wide along the far turn, re-rallied in the stretch, was gaining in the final furlong but was unable to impact the top three. MOONSHINE CAT allowed to settle in the early running, raced two wide into the backstretch run, was steered three wide into the far turn, mounted a four wide rally into the stretch, made a mild gain at the furlong marker, was gaining in the final stages but was unable to threaten. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE START OF THE RACE. THE STEWARDS DETERMINED THAT SPANISH CHANNEL IMPEDED DANGEROUS ILLUSION LEAVING THE BREAK, COSTING DANGEROUS ILLUSION THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING AND UNANIMOUSLY RULED THAT SPANISH CHANNEL BE DISQUALIFIED FROM SECOND AND PLACED THIRD FOR INTERFERENCE.

ENTRY.NAME: Dangerous Illusion
ENTRY.COMMENT: took up start,saved ground,full of run 1/8,finished well,mssd 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1 1/16M Turf CR: 85. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 1 Allowed 2 lbs . (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOLD DAUGHTER settled off of the early pace, raced outside of rivals along the first turn and came four wide into the backstretch run, improved position heading to the half-mile marker, was coaxed three then four wide along the second turn, advanced and came within aim at mid-stretch, confronted FINNLEY'S KITTEN nearing the sixteenth-marker, drifted in under firm hand urging in deep stretch, bumped FINNLEY'S KITTEN and surged in the final strides to prevail. FINNLEY'S KITTEN broke alertly and was prominent in the early running, ceded the lead to LYINATTHEBAR into the first turn and stalked that rival through moderate fractions into the backstretch run, attended to the pace into the far turn, was roused two wide heading to the quarter marker, assumed command at the top of the lane, was set down at mid-stretch, switched to the left lead inside of the furlong pole, was confronted by BOLD DAUGHTER nearing the sixteenth-pole, battled against that rival to deep stretch, was bumped and forced in a path by the drifting BOLD DAUGHTER and was outfinished in the final strides, while just holding for second. COUNCILWOMAN JILLY settled just off of the early pace, raced three wide along the first turn, maintained her position through the backstretch run, was coaxed along two wide into the second turn, came in a bit tight and waited for racing room approaching the top of the stretch, angled three wide for the drive, closed willingly in the stretch and just missed for second at the finish. ELA CALIMERA MOU unhurried in the early running, raced two wide into the backstretch run, was steered four wide into the far turn, made a steady gain to the quarter marker, was roused five wide into the stretch, continued to gain heading to mid-stretch, lacked a final response in the drive and was outkicked. LYINATTHEBAR forwardly placed in the early running, assumed command into the first turn, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, showed the way to the quarter marker, was overtaken in upper stretch, chased to the furlong marker and gave way in the late stages. KOKO'S MOM settled off of the early pace while not far back, improved position on the backstretch run while saving ground, continued her rail trip along the far turn, ran evenly into the stretch and did not produce a late rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Councilwoman Jilly
ENTRY.OWNER: Sido Racing Partners LLC Freeman Cassie and Freeman Keenan

ENTRY.NAME: Koko's Mom
ENTRY.OWNER: Clark Parker and William Burke Equine LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,never far back,saved ground,evenly 1/8,no late rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M All Weather Track CR: 75. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered I n Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOS VICIOS was forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the moderate fractions into the backstretch run, attended to the pace to the half-mile pole, advanced to confront NEVER HAD I EVER at the quarter marker, took command into upper stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong grounds, had the lead cut into a bit in the final stages but kept to task in deep stretch and held safely for the win. EFFECTIVE GIG was unhurried early on, saved ground while trailing through the backstretch run, was steered three then four wide along the second turn, swung widest into the drive, chased DOS VICIOS to mid-stretch, was able to cut into that rival's margin in deep stretch but could not reel him in and was outfinished, while holding well in the end for second. WILD BILLY D lunged at the start and was off a step slowly, settled off of the early pace and raced between rivals into the first turn, was never far back through the backstretch run, continued to run between foes into the second turn, advanced two wide nearing the quarter marker, lost a bit of ground heading to mid-stretch, re-rallied in the final stages but was outclosed by EFFECTIVE GIG and missed for second. SNAKE ISLAND settled just off of the early pace while not far back, stalked the moderate fractions from a ground saving position through the backstretch run, advanced along the rail on the second turn, was outrun into upper stretch and weakened in the drive. EXTRA INNINGS hopped leaving the start and was away a bit slowly, tracked the early pace while three deep on the first turn, advanced outside of rivals along the backstretch run, mounted a three wide bid at the quarter marker, could not sustain that bid into the stretch and gave way. NEVER HAD I EVER broke alertly and dictated terms in the early going, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure nearing the quarter marker, was overtaken leaving the far turn and tired in the stretch drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Snake Island
ENTRY.OWNER: Strohmaier Racing Lovett John Mathis Andy Porreca Anthony Start Donn and Underwo
ENTRY.COMMENT: not far back early,stalked inside,gain 1/4,weakened stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5F Turf CR: 92. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIGHTINTHEDARKNESS broke alertly, showed good early speed and dueled for pace duties into the turn, shook free along the bend and carved out fast fractions to the quarter pole, drifted out to the three path in upper stretch, held foes at bay to the furlong grounds, kept to task to deep stretch, was fully extended in the final strides and lasted for the win at the finish. AMANOFMYSTATURE tracked the fast early pace from the second flight, saved ground while advancing on the turn, swung four wide into the stretch, improved position at the furlong marker, rallied in the late stages, came within aim of LIGHTINTHEDARKNESS in the final strides and just missed for the win, while holding safely for second. IMPLICITLY allowed to settle in the early running, advanced three wide on the turn, swung six wide into the stretch, continued to gain ground to mid-stretch, finished well inside of the furlong marker while widest, shifted in in deep stretch, could not reel in the top two in the final stages and was up in time to secure third. OBVIOUS forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the fast pace from a two wide path on the turn, came four wide into the stretch, chased to the furlong pole, was outkicked in the final stages and was outfinished for third. HAY JUAN was prominent in the early running, pressed the quick pace to the turn, drifted out on the bend and lost ground approaching the quarter pole, came five wide into the stretch, chased to the furlong grounds and lacked a late rally. DEALERS HAND chased the quick early pace, lost position while two wide on the turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, was gaining late but did not threaten. MR. CLUTCH chased the fast early pace, lost position on the turn while saving ground and lacked a late response. FULLY LOADED broke in the air at the start, spotted the field in the early stages and trailed to the turn, showed late interest in the stretch and made up ground in the final furlong but did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 6F All Weather Track CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHAOKOON tracked the fast early pace from the inside, improved position along the turn, was roused three wide into the stretch, loomed at the furlong marker, overtook BRONZE ONE nearing the sixteenth-pole and drove clear in the late stages. BRONZE ONE sent to show early speed, dictated terms to the turn and opened to a clear lead heading to the bend, carved out quick fractions to the quarter marker, felt pressure from CHAOKOON nearing the furlong pole, was overtaken approaching the sixteenth-marker and could not keep pace with the winner in the late stages while besting the rest. WEE BEASTIE chased from the second flight in the early going, saved ground to the quarter pole, angled four wide into upper stretch, was not able to impact the top two and finished evenly in the drive while holding for third at the finish. ONE LITTLE INDIAN off slowly leaving the start, lacked early speed heading to the turn, raced two wide to the quarter marker, improved position at mid-stretch, was gaining in the final stages and missed for third. ONE BIG SMILE broke out at the start and crowded ANTICIPATED, chased the fast early pace, raced outside of rivals along the turn, swung four wide into the stretch, was outrun to the furlong pole and lacked a late rally. ANTICIPATED was crowded at the start by ONE BIG SMILE and was away slowly, trailed in the early running, saved ground to the quarter marker and did not threaten in the stretch. CASH'S CAT chased the fast early pace, lost position on the turn while two wide, came three wide into the stretch and tired in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alcatraz S. GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 101. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. By subscription of $50 each to accompany the nomination or by supplementary nomination of $1,250 at the time of entry which includes all fees. $750 to enter with $75,000 Guaranteed. Weight: 120 lbs. Highest earnings preferred. No minations closed Friday, May 19, 2023 with 18 nominations. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GAME TIME broke well, assumed command into the first turn, was well handled while setting comfortable fractions through the first half mile, maintained the lead through the far turn, responded to intermittent urging down the late and was widening at the finish. COUSIN RICHIE was keen to run on early but did not fight the rider, tracked GAME TIME down the backstretch and through the far turn, was put into a drive passing the quarter pole, came into the stretch on the wrong lead, and had trouble changing leads throughout the stretch run but held on well for second. PRINCE ABU DHABI lagged at the back of the compact field through the early stages slipped through an opening on the rail heading into the far turn, made a nice run through the turn to get into contention, swung out to the three path for the stretch run, had trouble changing leads down the stretch but still ran on well to just miss second. PHOSPHORESCENCE (FR) broke best but ceded the lead to GAME TIME into the clubhouse turn, was content to track from the middle of the field to the far turn, lost some ground as the pace quickened then ran on well but was unable to improve. PASSARANDO raced two wide into the first turn, was being asked to stay close to the pace down the backstretch, responded when put into a drive with about three furlongs to run and maintained the run but was unable to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 6F All Weather Track CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIVERMORE HEAT raced mid-pack through the first quarter while being prompted to keep up, made a clean run in the two path through the turn, got a dream run turning for home and finished strongly under strong handling despite racing on the wrong lead through much of the stretch run. MOTOWN CLASSIC broke best, ceded the lead but raced up close while three wide, was put into a drive from the three-eighths, swung four wide into the stretch and finished up well enough to gain the place. DADDY'SDARLINGBOY broke well, attended the early pace just behind the lone pacesetter, moved up to engage passing the quarter pole with MOTOWN CLASSIC also challenging to the outside and LIVERMORE HEAT to the inside, held a brief lead at the top of the stretch but was outfinished. LUCKY RAPPER devoid of early speed, raced well behind for a half mile, responded to strong urging down the lane and was gaining ground in the end. NOTCH hopped at the start and was off a step slowly, lagged behind the field down the backstretch, came under a hard ride before the half mile marker, kept to task and advanced position in the late stages. EASTER COMMAND broke out at the start, tracked from well behind the early pace, held position to the turn then had nothing left for the stretch run. ANOTHER STRIKE broke in a tangle then was sent to the front once righted, was left alone on the lead to the turn while setting solid fractions, was challenged at the head of the stretch and gave way readily.
